{% call components.section("Usage") -%}

  <p>A cookie banner informs visitors that the website they’re browsing uses cookie data. A cookie banner is required to be displayed for all users that have not previously closed the banner on other pages of the website. Cookie banner rules are standardized per country and must meet all regulations for cookie compliance. Rules of using the cookie banner exist outside of the design system and should be managed by a third party.</p>

  <h3>Grid</h3>
  <p>A cookie banner doesn’t fall within the grid, it spans almost the entire width of a browser window on any screen size.<p>

  <h3>Layout</h3>
  <p>A cookie banner contains legal information that should be placed on the bottom of a page so it doesn’t take away from the more important content on top. It’s still important enough to warrant persistence in order to ensure that visitors see it.</p>

  <img src="http://www.placehold.it/1200x300"/>

{%- endcall %}

<hr class="margin-top--2 margin-bottom--10">

